messages.text: R u coming to the cocktail party tonight?
Just have to check in to my room.
Why r u staying so far away?
Ur the maid-of-honor. U should be with the rest of the bridal party.
I don’t have anyone to split a room with :-/.
U could stay with Tim and me.
Thanks for the pity offer but no thanks.
I hear Brian’s got a brother who’s single.
And you know how rich the family is :).
So I could be Emily’s sister-in-law?
YOU’RE SUPPOSED TO BE HER BEST FRIEND!
We’re all going to get our nails done.
Oh. Emily asked if I would give a toast at the wedding.
I thought that was the maid-of-honor’s job?
But she thought you could give yours tonight at the rehearsal dinner.
Ok. If that’s what she wants.
Does Brian look happy to you?
Sure. Why wouldn’t he? He’s about to get married.
Idk. He just seemed kind of quiet last night.
How well do u know him?
We always got along really well.
I don’t think Emily has any.
They didn’t even sign a pre-nup.
She’s going to be so rich.
Do u think they’re good for each other?
Marriage isn’t about love. It’s about comfort and stability.
Plus Emily is really good at keeping him in line.
Sure you don’t want to get ur nails done?
Emily is not happy with you.
I just said what you said.
That’s not what you say on the eve of someone’s wedding!
Now Emily is embarrassed and won’t come out of her room.
And no one knows where Brian is!
Tell him to come be with his bride!
U need to make this right.
Well, good thing you’re making a speech at the actual wedding.
No one can find Brian and the wedding is supposed to start in ten minutes.
U were supposed to be back with flowers an hour ago and the groom is missing!
But the wedding is happening right now!
What’s going on is I’m doing something for me.
I’m going to go have the time of my life.
I’m going to have a rich boyfriend.
Screw Emily and her perfect life.
Now she knows what it’s like for something to go wrong.
And when I talked to him by the lake last night…
What am I supposed to say?
Idk. Use something from ur speech.
